A disgruntled McDonald's customer has been charged with assault after she allegedly grabbed a young worker by the neck because she was unhappy with the fries she ordered.

The 38-year-old woman was a passenger in a BMW when she went through the McDonald's drive-through at Stanmore in Sydney's inner west on Tuesday night.

When she received her food from the 16-year-old girl at the drive-through hatch, the woman allegedly threw it back into the window and demanded a new order.

