The young female employee asked the driver to pull into the waiting bay while a new order was prepared.

But the woman then allegedly got out of the car and entered the store yelling at the teenager.

Police say she grabbed the 16-year-old by the neck and scratched her face before the 21-year-old manager intervened to stop her. 

The manager grabbed the woman's hand and she allegedly scratched his arm before police were called and arrested her at the scene. 

